# TSA Data Analysis Project Structure

This project consists of two main Python scripts and supporting files:

## Core Scripts
- [tsa_scraper.py](mdc:tsa_scraper.py): Main script for scraping TSA passenger volume data. Handles both historical data (2019 onwards) and current year data differently. Creates/updates CSV files for each year.
- [tsa_visualizer.py](mdc:tsa_visualizer.py): Visualization script that generates three different plots from the collected data.

## Supporting Files
- [requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt): Lists all Python package dependencies
- [README.md](mdc:README.md): Project documentation and usage instructions

## Data Files
- CSV files are generated in the format `tsa_passengers_YYYY.csv` where YYYY is the year
- Each CSV contains daily passenger counts with Date and Passengers columns

## Generated Visualizations
The visualizer creates three PNG files:
- tsa_daily_trends.png: Shows raw passenger volumes over time
- tsa_monthly_averages.png: Shows monthly patterns
- tsa_weekly_patterns.png: Shows day-of-week patterns
